parameters.usage:
Possible values:
	**chart**  Set the mode for all charts of all users in this server. While this is set any user configuration will be overridden.
		The possible values for the chart mode are the following:
			**Image**: Using the standard image format
			**Image-info**: Adds additional info to better identify the user of the chart
			**Image-aside**: Shows titles on the side of the chart
			**Image-aside-info**: Image Info and Aside Together
			**List**: Shows it on a embed
			**Pie**: Shows using a pie chart
			**Clear**: Sets the default mode 
	**crowns**  A positive number that represent the minimum number of scrobbles for a crown to count
	**np-reactions**  Whether you want the bot to add reactions to nps in this server.
	**override-reactions**  Whether you want the server reactions to override the users reactions, add to the user added or only use them when the user doesnt have any.
		The possible values for the override np mode are the following:
			**Override**: Override all reactions with the server reactions
			**Add**: Adds server reactions before the user reactions
			**Add-End**: Adds server reactions after the user reactions
			**Empty**: Only overrides if the user doesnt have any reaction set
	**override-color**  Whether you want the server color to override the users colors or only use them when the user doesnt have any.
		The possible values for the color mode are the following:
			**Override**: Override all colors with the server colors
			**Empty**: Only overrides if the user doesnt have any color set
	**delete-message**  Whether you want the bot to delete the original message the user wrote.
	**np**  Setting this will alter the appearance of this server np commands. You can select any from the following list and mix them up:
CLEAR | Normal | Previous | Tags | Crown | Lfm-Listeners | Lfm-Scrobbles | Album-Rym | Artist-Rank | Server-Album-Rym | Bot-Album-Rym | Album-Rank | Album-Crown | Global-Crown | Global-Rank | Global-Album-Crown | Global-Album-Rank | Server-Listeners | Server-Scrobbles | Gender | Country | Artist-Pic | Random | Album-Plays | Artist-Plays | Song-Plays | Highest-Streak | Highest-Server-Streak | Highest-Bot-Streak | Spotify-Link | Song-Duration | Bot-Listeners | Bot-Scrobbles | Track-Rank | Track-Crown | Global-Track-Crown | Global-Track-Rank | Extended-Tags | Current-Combo | Scrobble-Count | Rym-Link | Loved | Popularity
	**rest**  Set the mode for all charts of the remaining images of the users in this server. While this is set any user configuration will be overridden 
		The possible values for the rest of the commands are the following:
			**Image**: Using the standard image format
			**List**: Shows it on a embed
			**Pie**: Shows using a pie chart
			**Clear**: Sets the default mode
	**disabled-warning**  Whether you want the bot to show a warning when you try to run a disabled command.
	**color**  Set the color for all embed of all users in this server. While this is set any user configuration will be overridden.
		The possible values for the embed colour are the following:
			**Random**: Uses a random colour
			**Role**: Uses the color of your role in a server
			**Colours**: Uses user defined colours
	**whoknows**  Set the mode for all who knows of all users in this server. While this is set any user configuration will be overridden.
		The possible values for the who knows mode are the following:
			**Image**: Using the standard image format
			**List**: Shows it on a embed
			**Pie**: Shows using a pie chart
			**Clear**: Sets the default mode
	**voice-announcement-channel**  If set, the bot will send to this channel when a new song is started, as opposed to using the channel where the command was invoked.
	**voice-announcement-enabled**  Whether the bot should announce if it plays the next song or not
	**set-on-join**  Whether the bot should automatically set all known users when they join your server.
	**censor-covers**  Whether you want the bot to censor potentially nsfw album covers.

parameters.usage:
Possible values:
	**chart**  Set the mode for all charts. Keep in mind that if a server has a set value that will be prioritized.
		The possible values for the chart mode are the following:
			**Image**: Using the standard image format
			**Image-info**: Adds additional info to better identify the user of the chart
			**Image-aside**: Shows titles on the side of the chart
			**Image-aside-info**: Image Info and Aside Together
			**List**: Shows it on a embed
			**Pie**: Shows using a pie chart
			**Clear**: Sets the default mode
	**image-notify**  Whether you will get notified or not when a submitted image gets accepted (true = notify, false = don't)
	**private-update**  If you want others users to be able to update your account with a ping and the update command (true for making it private, false for it to be public)
	**whoknows**  Set the mode for all charts. Keep in mind that if a server has a set value that will be prioritized.
		The possible values for the who knows mode are the following:
			**Image**: Using the standard image format
			**List**: Shows it on a embed
			**Pie**: Shows using a pie chart
			**Clear**: Sets the default mode
	**rest**  Set the mode for the rest of the commands. Keep in mind that if a server has a set value that will be prioritized.
		The possible values for the rest of the commands are the following:
			**Image**: Using the standard image format
			**List**: Shows it on a embed
			**Pie**: Shows using a pie chart
			**Clear**:| Sets the default mode
	**size**  Change the default chart size for chart command when you dont specify directly the size
	**privacy**  Sets how will you appear in the global leaderboard, changing this means users from other servers might be able to contact you directly
	**rating-notify**  Whether you will get notified or not when a url you have submitted to the random command gets rated by someone else (true = notify, false = don't)
	**private-lastfm**  Setting this to true will mean that your last.fm name will stay private and will not be shared with anyone. (This is different from privacy settings since it affects commands within a server and not cross server)
	**show-botted**  Setting this to false will mean that you wont have to include --nobotted in the global commands to exclude accounts flagged as bots)
	**np**  Setting this will alter the appearance of your np commands. You can select as many as you want from the following list and mix them up:
Normal | Previous | Tags | Crown | Lfm-Listeners | Lfm-Scrobbles | Album-Rym | Artist-Rank | Server-Album-Rym | Bot-Album-Rym | Album-Rank | Album-Crown | Global-Crown | Global-Rank | Global-Album-Crown | Global-Album-Rank | Server-Listeners | Server-Scrobbles | Gender | Country | Artist-Pic | Random | Album-Plays | Artist-Plays | Song-Plays | Highest-Streak | Highest-Server-Streak | Highest-Bot-Streak | Spotify-Link | Song-Duration | Bot-Listeners | Bot-Scrobbles | Track-Rank | Track-Crown | Global-Track-Crown | Global-Track-Rank | Extended-Tags | Current-Combo | Scrobble-Count | Rym-Link | Loved | Popularity
	**scrobbling**  Setting this to false will mean that whatever you play with the bot on a voice channel won't scrooble
	**color**  Set the color for your embeds.
		The possible values for the embed colour are the following:
			**Random**: Uses a random colour
			**Role**: Uses the color of your role in a server
			**Colours**: Uses user defined colours
	**own-tags**  Setting this to true will mean that for the np command your own tags will be prioritized. (Need also to authorize the bot with `login`)
	**artist-threshold**  Changes the minimun number of plays required for an album to show on the artist command
	**chart-options**  Specify some chart options that will apply as default for all your charts. Right now only --plays and --notitles
	**timezone**  TIMEZONE
